It would make sense to handle outgoing mail from Confluence in a more unified way. In many cases people want to modify their email templates to fit in the corporate image and for this they have to do several modifications (Daily updates email, recommended updates, share page, etc).

If all plugins could use a common template-bundle that would make customizing email much more easier.

h4. Steps to Reproduce
# Create/Edit a Page
# Type \{office
# You'll notice that the powerpoint or viewppt macro has a missing icon:
!bonfire-screenshot-20121130-191851-272.png!

h4. Possible cause
There seems to be a typo in the CSS:
{code}
#autocomplete-dropdown .autocomplete-macros li.autocomplete-macro-viewdppt .icon,.macro-placeholder-icon-viewdppt {
    background-image: url(/s/en_GB/3391/c989735defd8798a9d5e69c058c254be2e5a762b.27/4.3.2/_/download/resources/com.atlassian.confluence.tinymceplugin:editor-content-styles/../../../images/icons/macrobrowser/dropdown/viewppt.png);
}
{code} 

h4. Workaround
(i) This might only work with Confluence 4.3.x (tested with Confluence 4.3.2)
Add the following in the Confluence Admin > Custom HTML > "At beginning of the BODY":
{code}
<style>
#autocomplete-dropdown .autocomplete-macros li.autocomplete-macro-viewppt .icon,.macro-placeholder-icon-viewppt
{
    background-image: url(../../../images/icons/macrobrowser/dropdown/viewppt.png) !important;
}
</style>
{code}

