confluence 4.3.1
https://wiki.duraspace.org/display/DSPACE/DSpace+Release+3.0+Notes

between v0.80 and 0.81 I added a number of numbered lists in table cells. When enabling/disabling some of these lists, all of the lists lower on the page got disabled as well.

h3.Steps to Reproduce
# Navigate to {{ConfluenceInstallationDirectory/conf}}, edit catalina.properties, and put this at the end of the file (see https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/CONF42/Configuring+Web+Proxy+Support+for+Confluence):
{code}
http.proxyHost=192.168.3.3
http.proxyPort=8900
{code}
# Restart Confluence, and navigate to {{Confluence Admin >> Atlassian Support Tools >> Log Scanner}}
# Startup Wireshark, and set the following *capture filter*:
{code}
tcp port 8900
{code}
# Start Capturing, before clicking on *Scan* in {{Confluence Admin >> Atlassian Support Tools >> Log Scanner}}

Notice that there are no packets to port 8900 (example above) that is captured when using the log scanner. To compare this, you can try to navigate to {{Confluence Admin >> Manage Add-Ons}}, notice that there will be quite a number of port 8900 packets that are captured. 

h3.Important Note

This behavior is *not present in Confluence 4.2*. In fact, if we use the same methods described above in Confluence 4.2, port 8900 packets will be captured during log scans. So this proves that the log scanner does not pass through the web proxy in Confluence 4.3 (tested with 4.3.1 and 4.3.3).

With this limitation, many of our customers' instances that are located behind a web proxy will not be able to benefit from the log scanner functionality, thus increasing contact rates.
